---
import PresentationLayout from '~/layouts/PresentationLayout.astro';

const metadata = {
  title: 'Coding Agents 101: Foundation and Mindset',
  description:
    'An introduction to coding agents and the foundational mindset needed to work effectively with AI-powered development tools.',
  ignoreTitleTemplate: false,
};
---

<PresentationLayout metadata={metadata}>
  <section data-state="title" class="title-slide">
    <h1>Coding Agents 101</h1>
    <h2>Foundation and Mindset</h2>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Agenda</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>AI in Development</li>
      <li>Why integrations fail</li>
      <li>Foundations</li>
      <li>Best Practices</li>
      <li>Short Demo</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <section>
      <h2>AI in Development</h2>
    </section>
    <section>
      <h3>Possibilities</h3>
      <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 1.5rem; margin-top: 2rem;">
        <div class="content-box">
          <span class="content-box-icon">🧪</span>
          <div class="content-box-content">
            <h3>Test Generation</h3>
            <p style="color: #a0aec0;">Generating Unit, Integration and E2E tests</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="content-box fragment">
          <span class="content-box-icon">👁️</span>
          <div class="content-box-content">
            <h3>Code Reviews</h3>
            <p style="color: #a0aec0;">Acceptance Criteria, Performance, Guidelines</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="content-box fragment">
          <span class="content-box-icon">⚡</span>
          <div class="content-box-content">
            <h3>Code Generation</h3>
            <p style="color: #a0aec0;">Code generation at all levels</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="content-box fragment">
          <span class="content-box-icon">✨</span>
          <div class="content-box-content">
            <h3>And more...</h3>
            <p style="color: #a0aec0;">Documentation, refactoring, bug fixes</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
    <section>
      <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 2rem; align-items: start;">
        <div>
          <h3>The Hype</h3>
          <ul style="list-style: none;">
            <li>❌ AI builds features autonomously</li>
            <li>❌ AI replaces developers</li>
            <li>❌ 10x productivity overnight</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="fragment">
          <h3>Reality</h3>
          <ul style="list-style: none;">
            <li>✅ AI helps <strong>YOU</strong> building features</li>
            <li>✅ AI empowers software engineers</li>
            <li>✅ >2x productivity with proper setup</li>
            <li>⚠️ <1x if used incorrectly</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
    <section>
      <h2>The "Junior Developer" Mental Model</h2>
      <p>Think of AI as a talented junior developer on your team.</p>
      <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 3rem; margin-top: 2rem; align-items: start;">
        
        <div>
          <h3>Junior devs need:</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Good examples to follow</li>
            <li>Clear boundaries</li>
            <li>Code review</li>
            <li>Specific tasks</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div>
          <h3>AI needs the same:</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Strong codebase patterns</li>
            <li>Well-defined scope</li>
            <li>Your oversight</li>
            <li>Focused objectives</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        
      </div>
    </section>
  </section>

  <section>
    <section>
      <h2>What can go wrong?</h2>
      <h3>Why integrations fail?</h3>
    </section>

    <section>
      <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 2rem;">
        <div class="content-box red">
          <span class="content-box-icon">🌪️</span>
          <div class="content-box-content">
            <h3>Integrating AI everywhere at once</h3>
            <p style="color: #a0aec0;"><strong>Why it fails:</strong> No baseline to measure success, overwhelming to maintain</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="content-box red fragment">
          <span class="content-box-icon">🤖</span>
          <div class="content-box-content">
            <h3>Generating guidelines with AI</h3>
            <p style="color: #a0aec0;"><strong>Why it fails:</strong> AI doesn't understand your context deeply enough</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="content-box red fragment">
          <span class="content-box-icon">🏗️</span>
          <div class="content-box-content">
            <h3>Big refactoring tasks</h3>
            <p style="color: #a0aec0;"><strong>Why it fails:</strong> Too much context, too many decisions, high risk</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="content-box red fragment">
          <span class="content-box-icon">🎯</span>
          <div class="content-box-content">
            <h3>Feature one-shot generation</h3>
            <p style="color: #a0aec0;"><strong>Why it fails:</strong> Features need iteration, edge cases, business context</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="fragment" style="border: 2px solid #f0c36d; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.5rem; background: rgba(240, 195, 109, 0.15);">
        <p style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem; margin: 0;">
          <span style="font-size: 1.5rem;">⚠️</span>
          <strong>The Pattern: Lack of Foundation</strong> — All of these fail because they skip the foundational work.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </section>

  <section>
    <section>
      <h2>Building the Foundation</h2>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h3>1. Your Workflow Comes First</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Map your existing development workflow</li>
        <li>Identify pain points and high-value targets</li>
        <li>Only then consider where AI fits</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h3>2. Your Codebase = Training Data</h3>
      <p style="color: #a0aec0; margin-bottom: 2rem;">AI is pattern-matching, not magic</p>
      <div class="fragment">
        <p style="font-size: 2.5rem; font-weight: 700; color: #0ea5c1; margin: 2rem 0;">
          Garbage In ⇒ Garbage Out
        </p>
        <p style="font-size: 1.1rem; color: #a0aec0;">
          Your codebase quality directly determines AI output quality.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h3 style="margin-bottom: 1rem;">3. The 3-Layer Approach</h3>
      <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1rem;">
        <div style="border: 3px solid #4ade80; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1rem 1.25rem; background: rgba(74, 222, 128, 0.1); position: relative;">
          <span style="position: absolute; top: 0.75rem; right: 1rem; background: white; color: black; padding: 0.35rem 0.75rem; border-radius: 6px; font-weight: 700; font-size: 0.75rem;">Most Important</span>
          <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0.35rem; font-size: 1.3rem;">Layer 1: Codebase</h3>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 0.35rem; font-size: 1rem;"><strong>Consistency and good examples</strong></p>
          <p style="font-style: italic; color: #a0aec0; font-size: 0.9rem;">Example: Existing handlers show the pattern</p>
        </div>

        <div class="fragment" style="border: 3px solid #0ea5c1; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1rem 1.25rem; background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.1); position: relative;">
          <span style="position: absolute; top: 0.75rem; right: 1rem; background: white; color: black; padding: 0.35rem 0.75rem; border-radius: 6px; font-weight: 700; font-size: 0.75rem;">Supplements</span>
          <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0.35rem; font-size: 1.3rem;">Layer 2: Guidelines</h3>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 0.35rem; font-size: 1rem;"><strong>Navigates, restricts, clarifies</strong></p>
          <p style="font-style: italic; color: #a0aec0; font-size: 0.9rem;">Example: Use error middleware, validate with Zod</p>
        </div>

        <div class="fragment" style="border: 3px solid #f0c36d; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1rem 1.25rem; background: rgba(240, 195, 109, 0.1); position: relative;">
          <span style="position: absolute; top: 0.75rem; right: 1rem; background: white; color: black; padding: 0.35rem 0.75rem; border-radius: 6px; font-weight: 700; font-size: 0.75rem;">Quality Check</span>
          <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0.35rem; font-size: 1.3rem;">Layer 3: References</h3>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 0.35rem; font-size: 1rem;"><strong>Gold standard examples</strong></p>
          <p style="font-style: italic; color: #a0aec0; font-size: 0.9rem;">Example: Point to best handler as reference</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Best Practices That Work</h2>
    <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1rem; margin-top: 1.5rem;">
      <div class="content-box">
        <span class="content-box-icon">🌱</span>
        <div class="content-box-content">
          <h3>Start Small</h3>
          <p style="color: #a0aec0;">Begin with unit tests or simple HTTP handlers</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="content-box fragment">
        <span class="content-box-icon">📋</span>
        <div class="content-box-content">
          <h3>Make Examples First</h3>
          <p style="color: #a0aec0;">Create one perfect example, then let AI replicate</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="content-box fragment">
        <span class="content-box-icon">🔄</span>
        <div class="content-box-content">
          <h3>Test and Refine</h3>
          <p style="color: #a0aec0;">Iterate on guidelines based on actual output</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="content-box fragment">
        <span class="content-box-icon">📈</span>
        <div class="content-box-content">
          <h3>Scale Gradually</h3>
          <p style="color: #a0aec0;">Expand only after proving it works</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>What is next?</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Define high-value starting point (e.g. Unit Tests, HTTP handlers)</li>
      <li>Prepare good examples (e.g. 5 strong test cases)</li>
      <li>Craft strong guidelines</li>
      <li>Start using AI Agent</li>
      <li>Refine & Improve</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Thank you!</h2>
  </section>
</PresentationLayout>
